ResultHash: B39A9428CF5215E753630CB05CD26F180B0A4F32
~~~~~
Account Lockout Configuration Check (CAT I)
============================================

RESULT: FINDING - No account lockout mechanism configured.

Neither pam_faillock nor pam_tally2 module is configured in PAM files.

Files checked:
  - /etc/pam.d/system-auth
  - /etc/pam.d/password-auth

REMEDIATION:
Configure pam_faillock in /etc/pam.d/system-auth and /etc/pam.d/password-auth:
  auth required pam_faillock.so preauth deny=3 unlock_time=900 fail_interval=900
  auth required pam_faillock.so authfail deny=3 unlock_time=900 fail_interval=900

XCP-ng Version: XCP-ng 8.3.0
</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/09/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
XCP-ng Dom0 does not properly enforce login attempt limits. The automated check found that pam_faillock.so is not configured or parameters do not meet requirements.

Remediation:
1. Edit /etc/pam.d/system-auth and /etc/pam.d/password-auth to include:
   auth required pam_faillock.so preauth deny=3 fail_interval=900 unlock_time=never
   auth required pam_faillock.so authfail deny=3 fail_interval=900 unlock_time=never
2. Verify: faillock --user testuser
3. Test by attempting 4 failed logins and confirming lockout

Contact the system administrator to configure PAM faillock.

</COMMENTS>
