				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/09/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
XCP-ng Dom0 does not protect audit information from unauthorized deletion.

The automated check found /var/log/audit/ directory permissions allow unauthorized deletion.

Remediation:
1. Set directory permissions: chmod 700 /var/log/audit
2. Set ownership: chown root:root /var/log/audit
3. Configure log retention in auditd.conf: max_log_file_action = keep_logs
4. Verify: stat -c "%a %U %G" /var/log/audit

Contact the system administrator to protect audit logs from deletion.

</COMMENTS>
