				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/09/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
XCP-ng does not properly protect PKI private keys.

The automated check found private key files with overly permissive access.

Remediation:
1. Set XAPI key permissions: chmod 600 /etc/xensource/xapi-ssl.pem; chown root:root /etc/xensource/xapi-ssl.pem
2. Set SSH key permissions: chmod 600 /etc/ssh/ssh_host_*_key; chown root:root /etc/ssh/ssh_host_*_key
3. Verify: stat -c "%a %U" /etc/xensource/xapi-ssl.pem /etc/ssh/ssh_host_*_key

Contact the system administrator to restrict private key access.

</COMMENTS>
