Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
XCP-ng does not properly map PKI-authenticated identities to accounts.

The automated check found that PKI-based authentication mapping is not configured.

Remediation:
1. Enable public key authentication in /etc/ssh/sshd_config: PubkeyAuthentication yes
2. Configure authorized keys: AuthorizedKeysFile .ssh/authorized_keys
3. For AD integration, configure SSSD with certificate mapping
4. Restart sshd: systemctl restart sshd

Contact the system administrator and PKI administrator to configure identity mapping.

