Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
XCP-ng does not disable inactive accounts after 35 days.

The automated check found INACTIVE is not set to 35 or less in /etc/default/useradd, or existing accounts lack inactivity limits.

Remediation:
1. Set default: useradd -D -f 35
2. Apply to existing accounts: chage -I 35 username
3. Verify: useradd -D | grep INACTIVE; chage -l username

Contact the system administrator to configure account inactivity limits.

