Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
XCP-ng does not meet federal cryptographic module authentication requirements.

The automated check found FIPS mode is not enabled. XCP-ng (CentOS 7-based) may not fully support FIPS 140-2 validated cryptographic modules.

Remediation:
1. Enable FIPS mode: fips-mode-setup --enable (if supported)
2. Verify: cat /proc/sys/crypto/fips_enabled (should be 1)
3. If FIPS mode is not supported, document as a compliance gap in POA&amp;M
4. Use FIPS-validated crypto libraries where available

Contact the ISSO to document FIPS compliance status.

