				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/09/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
XCP-ng does not automatically remove or disable emergency accounts within 72 hours.

The automated check found accounts without expiration dates or emergency account policies not enforced.

Remediation:
1. Set expiration on emergency accounts: chage -E $(date -d "+3 days" +%Y-%m-%d) emergency_user
2. Configure default expiration: useradd -D -e DATE
3. Create procedures for emergency account lifecycle
4. Review accounts regularly: chage -l username

Contact the ISSO to establish emergency account procedures.

</COMMENTS>
