RESULT: PCI passthrough devices detected. These bypass VMM mediation and allow direct hardware access from guest VMs. Verify each passthrough device is authorized and documented.</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/09/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
PCI passthrough devices were detected that bypass VMM mediation for guest VM interactions.

The automated check found one or more VMs with direct PCI device passthrough, which allows guest VMs to access physical hardware directly without XAPI/Xen mediation. This violates the VMM SRG requirement that all VM interactions be mediated by the VMM.

Remediation:
1. Review all PCI passthrough assignments: xe vm-list params=name-label,other-config
2. Remove unauthorized PCI passthrough: xe vm-param-remove param-name=other-config param-key=pci uuid=VM_UUID
3. Document any authorized passthrough devices in the System Security Plan with ISSO/ISSM approval
4. Use XAPI-managed virtual devices (VIFs, VBDs) instead of direct hardware passthrough where possible

Contact the ISSO/ISSM to review and approve any remaining PCI passthrough requirements.

</COMMENTS>
				<SEVERITY_OVERRIDE />
				<SEVERITY_JUSTIFICATION />
