Audit  Account Modification
XCP-ng Version: XCP-ng 8.3.0

Audit rules monitoring account modification files:
  [FAIL] /etc/passwd  NOT monitored
  [FAIL] /etc/shadow  NOT monitored
  [FAIL] /etc/group  NOT monitored
  [FAIL] /etc/gshadow  NOT monitored

Command auditing:
  usermod: NOT monitored
  chage: NOT monitored

RESULT: 4 account modification file(s) not monitored by auditd. Add audit rules for: /etc/passwd, /etc/shadow, /etc/group, /etc/gshadow</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/09/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
One or more critical account files are not monitored by auditd for modification events.

The automated check found that auditd rules do not fully cover account modification files (/etc/passwd, /etc/shadow, /etc/group, /etc/gshadow). Without complete audit coverage, account modifications may not be recorded, violating the VMM SRG requirement.

Remediation:
1. Add audit rules to /etc/audit/rules.d/account-modification.rules:
   -w /etc/passwd -p wa -k identity
   -w /etc/shadow -p wa -k identity
   -w /etc/group -p wa -k identity
   -w /etc/gshadow -p wa -k identity
2. Reload audit rules: augenrules --load
3. Verify rules are active: auditctl -l | grep identity
4. Restart auditd if needed: service auditd restart

Contact the system administrator to implement these audit rules.

</COMMENTS>
				<SEVERITY_OVERRIDE />
				<SEVERITY_JUSTIFICATION />
