Audit  Account Disabling Actions
XCP-ng Version: XCP-ng 8.3.0

Audit rules for account disabling:
  /etc/shadow: NOT monitored
  /etc/passwd: NOT monitored
  usermod: NOT monitored
  /usr/bin/passwd: NOT monitored

RESULT: Account disabling actions not fully audited. Add audit rules for /etc/shadow and /etc/passwd to capture account lock/disable events.</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/09/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
Account disabling actions are not fully audited on XCP-ng Dom0.

The automated check found that auditd does not monitor /etc/shadow and/or /etc/passwd for write operations. Without these rules, account lock/disable events (passwd -l, usermod -L) are not recorded in the audit log.

Remediation:
1. Add audit rules to /etc/audit/rules.d/account-disable.rules:
   -w /etc/shadow -p wa -k identity
   -w /etc/passwd -p wa -k identity
2. Reload audit rules: augenrules --load
3. Verify: auditctl -l | grep -E "shadow|passwd"
4. Test by locking a test account and confirming audit log entry: ausearch -k identity

Contact the system administrator to implement these audit rules.

</COMMENTS>
