RESULT: Direct hardware passthrough detected (USB, GPU, or SR-IOV). These devices bypass VMM mediation. Verify each passthrough assignment is authorized and documented.</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/09/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
Direct hardware passthrough was detected that bypasses VMM mediation for VM-external interactions.

The automated check found USB passthrough, GPU passthrough, or SR-IOV configurations that allow guest VMs direct access to physical hardware without XAPI/Xen mediation. This violates the VMM SRG requirement for mediated VM-external interactions.

Remediation:
1. Review USB passthrough: xe pusb-list
2. Review GPU groups: xe gpu-group-list
3. Review SR-IOV networks: xe network-list params=name-label,other-config
4. Remove unauthorized passthrough assignments
5. Use XAPI-managed virtual devices instead where possible
6. Document any authorized passthrough in the System Security Plan with ISSO/ISSM approval

Contact the system administrator and ISSO to review all hardware passthrough configurations.

</COMMENTS>
