				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/09/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The auditd service is not properly configured to start at system boot.

The automated check found that auditd is not enabled at boot or is not currently active. Without auditd starting at boot, session events occurring during system startup are not audited, creating a gap in the audit trail.

Remediation:
1. Enable auditd at boot: systemctl enable auditd
2. Start auditd: service auditd start
3. Add audit=1 to kernel boot parameters in /etc/default/grub:
   GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX="... audit=1"
4. Rebuild grub: grub2-mkconfig -o /boot/grub2/grub.cfg
5. Verify: systemctl is-enabled auditd; systemctl is-active auditd

Contact the system administrator to enable auditd at boot.

</COMMENTS>
				<SEVERITY_OVERRIDE />
				<SEVERITY_JUSTIFICATION />
