Audit Records  Identity Information
XCP-ng Version: XCP-ng 8.3.0

auditd log format: default (RAW)

Total active audit rules: 1

RESULT: auditd is not active. Enable auditd to produce audit records with identity information.</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/09/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The audit system is not properly configured to produce records with identity information.

The automated check found that auditd is not active or has no configured audit rules. Without an active audit system, no records are produced to establish the identity of individuals or processes associated with security-relevant events.

Remediation:
1. Install auditd if missing: yum install audit
2. Enable and start: systemctl enable auditd; service auditd start
3. Add baseline audit rules: augenrules --load
4. Verify records include identity: ausearch -m USER_LOGIN --start recent
5. Confirm uid, auid, pid fields in audit log: tail /var/log/audit/audit.log

Contact the system administrator to configure the audit subsystem.

</COMMENTS>
