RESULT: Audit tools have improper access permissions. Ensure all audit binaries are owned by root with permissions no more permissive than 755.</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/09/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
Audit tools have improper access permissions on XCP-ng Dom0.

The automated check found audit binaries or log files with permissions more permissive than required, or not owned by root. This allows unauthorized users to access audit functions or read audit data.

Remediation:
1. Set correct ownership: chown root:root /sbin/auditctl /sbin/aureport /sbin/ausearch /sbin/autrace /sbin/auditd /sbin/augenrules
2. Set correct permissions: chmod 750 /sbin/auditctl /sbin/aureport /sbin/ausearch /sbin/autrace /sbin/auditd /sbin/augenrules
3. Protect audit log: chmod 600 /var/log/audit/audit.log; chown root:root /var/log/audit/audit.log
4. Verify: stat -c "%a %U %G" /sbin/audit*

Contact the system administrator to correct audit tool permissions.

</COMMENTS>
