				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/09/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
Audit tools may be modified by unauthorized users on XCP-ng Dom0.

The automated check found audit binaries or configuration files with group or world write permissions, or not owned by root. This allows non-root users to potentially modify audit tools or configuration.

Remediation:
1. Remove unauthorized write permissions from binaries: chmod go-w /sbin/auditctl /sbin/aureport /sbin/ausearch /sbin/autrace /sbin/auditd /sbin/augenrules
2. Secure configuration files: chmod 640 /etc/audit/auditd.conf /etc/audit/audit.rules; chown root:root /etc/audit/auditd.conf /etc/audit/audit.rules
3. Verify RPM integrity: rpm -V audit
4. Verify: stat -c "%a %U %G" /sbin/audit* /etc/audit/*.conf /etc/audit/*.rules

Contact the system administrator to correct audit tool permissions.

</COMMENTS>
