Password Complexity  Special Character Requirement
XCP-ng Version: XCP-ng 8.3.0

pwquality.conf ocredit setting:
  # ocredit = 1

PAM system-auth:
  password    requisite     pam_pwquality.so try_first_pass local_users_only retry=3 authtok_type=

PAM password-auth:
  password    requisite     pam_pwquality.so try_first_pass local_users_only retry=3 authtok_type=

RESULT: Password complexity does not require special characters. Set ocredit = -1 in /etc/security/pwquality.conf.</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/09/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
XCP-ng Dom0 does not enforce the special character requirement for password complexity.

The automated check found that ocredit is not set to -1 (or lower) in /etc/security/pwquality.conf or PAM configuration. Without this setting, passwords can be created without special characters, weakening password strength.

Remediation:
1. Edit /etc/security/pwquality.conf and set: ocredit = -1
2. Alternatively, add to /etc/pam.d/system-auth: password requisite pam_pwquality.so ... ocredit=-1
3. Verify the setting is active: grep ocredit /etc/security/pwquality.conf
4. Test by attempting to set a password without special characters

Contact the system administrator to configure password complexity requirements.

</COMMENTS>
				<SEVERITY_OVERRIDE />
				<SEVERITY_JUSTIFICATION />
