Account Creation Notification
XCP-ng Version: XCP-ng 8.3.0

External auth type: not configured
RBAC subjects: 0
Audit rules for account creation: not found

RESULT: No external authentication configured. XCP-ng does not natively notify SA/ISSO on account creation. Configure AD/LDAP integration via xe pool-enable-external-auth or implement organizational notification procedures.</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/09/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check found that XCP-ng pool does not have external authentication (AD/LDAP) configured to provide account creation notifications to SA/ISSO. Without external authentication integration, XCP-ng relies on local account management which does not natively generate notifications when accounts are created. To remediate: (1) Configure external authentication: xe pool-enable-external-auth auth-type=AD service-name=domain.example.com; (2) Configure AD Group Policy to notify SA/ISSO when new accounts are created (Event ID 4720); (3) Alternatively, configure auditd rules with email forwarding: auditctl -w /etc/passwd -p wa -k identity, combined with a mail alias for root to forward to SA/ISSO. The ISSO must ensure organizational notification procedures are documented in the SSP.

</COMMENTS>
				<SEVERITY_OVERRIDE />
				<SEVERITY_JUSTIFICATION />
