Account Modification Notification
XCP-ng Version: XCP-ng 8.3.0

External auth type: not configured
Audit rules for account modification: not found

RESULT: No external authentication configured. XCP-ng does not natively notify SA/ISSO on account modification. Configure AD/LDAP integration or implement organizational notification procedures.</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/09/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check found that XCP-ng pool does not have external authentication (AD/LDAP) configured to provide account modification notifications. Without AD integration, account modifications on local accounts do not generate notifications to SA/ISSO. To remediate: (1) Configure external authentication: xe pool-enable-external-auth auth-type=AD service-name=domain.example.com; (2) Configure AD monitoring for account modification events (Event IDs 4738, 4742); (3) Alternatively, configure auditd with mail forwarding for /etc/passwd and /etc/shadow changes. The ISSO must establish notification procedures for account modification events and document them in the System Security Plan.

</COMMENTS>
				<SEVERITY_OVERRIDE />
				<SEVERITY_JUSTIFICATION />
