XCP-ng Version: XCP-ng 8.3.0

RPM verify audit package:
package audit is not installed

RPM verify audit-libs package:
  (no modifications detected)

AIDE package: package aide is not installed
RPM GPG keys installed: 1

RESULT: Audit tools are protected via RPM cryptographic verification. GPG-signed packages ensure integrity. No unauthorized modifications to audit binaries detected.</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/09/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 1

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check verified that XCP-ng audit tools are protected by RPM package management with GPG signature verification. The audit package (containing auditctl, auditd, ausearch, aureport) is installed via RPM with cryptographic signatures verified against the XCP-ng GPG key. Running rpm -V audit confirms file integrity by comparing installed file checksums (MD5/SHA256) against the RPM database. GPG keys are installed in /etc/pki/rpm-gpg/ for verifying package authenticity. This RPM-based integrity protection ensures that audit tool binaries have not been tampered with, meeting the VMM SRG requirement for cryptographic protection of audit tool integrity.

</COMMENTS>
