Session Inactivity Timeout
XCP-ng Version: XCP-ng 8.3.0

SSH ClientAliveInterval: clientaliveinterval 0
SSH ClientAliveCountMax: clientalivecountmax 3
TMOUT setting: not configured

RESULT: SSH session inactivity timeout is not properly configured. Set ClientAliveInterval to 900 or less and ClientAliveCountMax to 0 in /etc/ssh/sshd_config.</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/09/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check found that session inactivity timeouts are not properly configured. SSH ClientAliveInterval is either not set or exceeds the DoD-required maximum (typically 600 seconds/10 minutes). To remediate: (1) Set SSH timeout in /etc/ssh/sshd_config: ClientAliveInterval 600 and ClientAliveCountMax 0; (2) Restart sshd: systemctl restart sshd; (3) Set shell timeout: echo "TMOUT=600; export TMOUT; readonly TMOUT" &gt; /etc/profile.d/tmout.sh; (4) Verify: source /etc/profile.d/tmout.sh. The system administrator must ensure all management interfaces enforce session inactivity timeouts per the organization-defined time period (typically 10-15 minutes for privileged sessions).

</COMMENTS>
