Wireless interfaces detected: none
Wireless kernel modules: dm_multipath           32768  0  dm_mod                151552  5 dm_multipath scsi_mod              253952  14 fcoe,scsi_dh_emc,scsi_transport_sas,sd_mod,dm_multipath,scsi_dh_alua,scsi_transport_fc,libfc,hpsa,bnx2fc,libata,sg,scsi_dh_rdac,scsi_dh_hp_sw

RESULT: Wireless interfaces or modules detected on this hypervisor host. DoD policy requires wireless access be protected with encryption. Wireless interfaces should be disabled on hypervisor hosts. Remove wireless kernel modules and disable any wireless interfaces.</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/09/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check detected wireless interfaces or wireless kernel modules on this XCP-ng hypervisor host. Wireless interfaces should not be present on server-class hypervisor systems per DoD security requirements. If wireless access must be used, it must be protected with WPA3 or equivalent FIPS-validated encryption. To remediate: (1) Remove wireless kernel modules: modprobe -r [module_name]; (2) Blacklist wireless modules: echo "blacklist [module_name]" &gt; /etc/modprobe.d/blacklist-wireless.conf; (3) Disable any wireless interfaces: ip link set [interface] down; (4) Remove wireless packages if installed: yum remove iw wireless-tools. Wireless interfaces on hypervisor hosts represent an unnecessary attack surface.

</COMMENTS>
