Account Enabling Notification
XCP-ng Version: XCP-ng 8.3.0

External auth type: not configured
Root mail alias: marc

RESULT: No external authentication (AD/LDAP) is configured to provide account enabling notifications to SA/ISSO. Configure external authentication via: xe pool-enable-external-auth auth-type=AD service-name=domain.example.com. Alternatively, configure auditd rules with email forwarding to notify SA/ISSO of account enabling actions.</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/09/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check found that XCP-ng pool does not have external authentication (AD/LDAP) configured to provide account enabling notifications to SA/ISSO. Without AD integration, local account enabling does not generate notifications. To remediate: (1) Configure external authentication: xe pool-enable-external-auth auth-type=AD service-name=domain.example.com; (2) Configure AD monitoring for account enable events (Event ID 4722); (3) Alternatively, configure auditd with mail forwarding for /etc/shadow changes combined with root mail alias to SA/ISSO. The ISSO must document notification procedures in the System Security Plan.

</COMMENTS>
