Privilege Level Enforcement
XCP-ng Version: XCP-ng 8.3.0

Xen Ring Architecture:
  Ring -1: Xen hypervisor (most privileged)
  Ring 0: Dom0 kernel (hardware access via Xen grants)
  Ring 3: Dom0 user space, DomU guest VMs (least privileged)

SUID binaries found: 18
/tmp mounted nosuid: False

RESULT: XCP-ng/Xen prevents software from executing at higher privilege levels through hardware-enforced ring architecture. Guest VMs (DomU) run in Ring 3 and cannot access Ring 0 (Dom0 kernel) or Ring -1 (Xen hypervisor). The Xen hypervisor mediates all hardware access through hypercalls. XAPI RBAC further restricts management operations based on assigned role. Software running within a guest VM cannot escalate to hypervisor or Dom0 privilege level.</FINDING_DETAILS>
