Account Lockout Policy
XCP-ng Version: XCP-ng 8.3.0

pam_faillock in system-auth: NOT configured
pam_faillock in password-auth: NOT configured
SSH MaxAuthTries: not set (default: 6)

RESULT: Account lockout is not properly configured to meet DoD requirements. Configure pam_faillock in /etc/pam.d/system-auth and /etc/pam.d/password-auth with: deny=3 fail_interval=900 unlock_time=0. Add to auth section: auth required pam_faillock.so preauth silent deny=3 fail_interval=900 unlock_time=0; auth required pam_faillock.so authfail deny=3 fail_interval=900 unlock_time=0</FINDING_DETAILS>
				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/09/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XCP-ng
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check found that account lockout is not properly configured on XCP-ng to meet DoD requirements. The pam_faillock module must be configured with deny &lt;= 3, fail_interval &gt;= 900, and unlock_time = 0. To remediate, add to /etc/pam.d/system-auth and /etc/pam.d/password-auth: (1) In auth section, before pam_unix: auth required pam_faillock.so preauth silent deny=3 fail_interval=900 unlock_time=0; (2) After pam_unix: auth required pam_faillock.so authfail deny=3 fail_interval=900 unlock_time=0; (3) In account section: account required pam_faillock.so. Verify with: faillock --user root. SSH MaxAuthTries should also be set to 3 or fewer in /etc/ssh/sshd_config.

</COMMENTS>
